text: The Fremantle railway line is a suburban railway line in Perth, Australia. It was opened in 1881 as part of the Eastern railway on the Western Australian Government Railways (WAGR). The line is a major transport route in Perth, connecting with the four other main Transperth railway lines: Joondalup, Midland, Armadale, and Mandurah. == Stations == There are a total of 17 stations along the Fremantle line. * Perth * City West * West Leederville * Subiaco * Daglish * Shenton Park * Karrakatta * Loch Street * Perth Showgrounds * Claremont * Swanbourne * Grant Street * Cottesloe * Mosman Park * Victoria Street * North Fremantle * Fremantle Category:Australian railways
title: Fremantle railway line, Perth
